legacy.full_text:
Prime Minister of #Australia #AnthonyAlbanese has kicked off his official visit to #China, which is the first by an Australian prime minister in seven years. Chinese President #XiJinping met with his Australian counterpart in #Beijing on Monday, November 6.
#China https://t.co/Wmc4T7vWHc

President Xi said China and Australia have “every reason to be partners” and Albanese echoed that dialogue and cooperation is “the right choice.” As ties warm, Australia also dispatched the largest-ever delegation to the ongoing 6th China International Import Expo. #CIIE2023

legacy.full_text: President Xi said PM Albanese’s visit this time indeed builds on past achievements & opens up new prospects.
